comments.text:
For the benefits of those who want to register for my class but are unable to do so for lack of vacancy, anyone who falls into two of the following categories, please, drop this course immediately because you will have to do so sooner or later: 

    you are a freeloader（混学分者）(hopefully not);
    you are a native speaker of English;
    you are a senior student (enrolled in 2017, 2016, 2015 or earlier) who will not study for a Master's Degree  or PHD  at Tsinghua or abroad;
    you are a freshman whose English placement test results belong in Band 2 and below;
    you are an athlete or an art student;
    your vocabulary size is below 65,00 (this is not compulsory but you have to work very hard to keep pace  with the   rest of  the class);
    you have registered for more than 26-credit classes (inclusive);
    you registered for this course but never intended to show up for class, and will not drop it until the last  minute to do so  (personally I do not understand why this is so);
    you cannot afford at least an hour a day on average to study the course materials and do your homework;
  you hold myths or wrong expectations about language learning;
  you may/might miss more than two classes (inclusive) without asking for leave;
  you know answers to more than 60% of the opening class questions.


It is for no other reason than that most of the above mentioned students will be too busy to put in enough time to study for the course, or you will not learn as much as expected, hence I strongly advise that you drop this course now immediately or as soon as possible.



Thank you for your understanding and cooperation!
